templates.file_state_schema:
## File State Schema
All file data — in AppState, ReadFiles responses, and EditFile responses — follows this single consistent structure:

```typescript
type CompressedFileState = {{
  id: number;
  name: string;         // effective name (pending renames applied)
  path: string;         // effective path
  type: 'question' | 'dashboard' | 'report' | 'alert' | 'folder' | string;
  isDirty: boolean;     // true if there are unpublished edits (user publishes via the Publish All button)
  content: QuestionContent | DashboardContent | ...;
    // merged saved + pending edits — use this directly for oldMatch in EditFile
}};

// Both ReadFiles and EditFile return this:
type CompressedAugmentedFile = {{
  fileState: CompressedFileState;
  references: CompressedFileState[];   // Referenced files (e.g. questions embedded in a dashboard)
  queryResults: CompressedQueryResult[];  // Cached query results (may be truncated — see below)
}};

type CompressedQueryResult = {{
  columns: string[];
  data: string;       // GFM markdown table — partial excerpt when truncated
  totalRows: number;  // full row count returned by the query
  shownRows: number;  // rows actually present in data (≤ totalRows)
  truncated: boolean; // true when data is a partial excerpt
  error?: string;     // set when query execution failed
}};
```

- **`content`** — the single merged view of saved state + any pending edits. Copy values directly from here as `oldMatch` in EditFile.
- **`isDirty`** — `true` when there are unpublished edits. After completing all edits, ask the user if they'd like to save changes (simple text is okay, no need for Clarify). Only when they confirm, call PublishAll to save.
- **`content.parameterValues`** — current parameter values stored in file content. Use EditFile to update them (e.g., `"parameterValues":{{"limit":100}}`). These ARE saved when the user publishes.
- **`queryResults` truncation** — AppState embeds a compact preview of query data (small limit). If `truncated: true` in AppState, call `ReadFiles` on the same file to get more rows (default 10k chars, up to 100k via `maxChars`). Chart image attachments in the conversation are always full-fidelity regardless of text truncation.

skill_dashboards.content:
## Instructions: Dashboards

### File Structure
```json
{{
  "assets": [
    {{"type": "question", "id": 123}},
    {{"type": "inline", "inlineType": "text", "content": "## Section Header\nSome markdown text"}},
    {{"type": "inline", "inlineType": "divider", "content": ""}},
    {{"type": "inline", "inlineType": "image", "content": "https://example.com/image.png"}}
  ],
  "layout": {{
    "columns": 12,
    "items": [
      {{"id": 123, "x": 0, "y": 0, "w": 6, "h": 4}},
      {{"id": "inline-0", "x": 6, "y": 0, "w": 6, "h": 2}}
    ]
  }}
}}
```
- Layout uses a 12-column grid. `x` is column offset, `y` is row offset, `w` is width, `h` is height.
- Question items have id `<questionId>`, inline items have id `inline-<index>`.
- When adding a question to a dashboard, you MUST simultaneously add it to the `assets` list and place it in the `layout`.
- Minimum width, height for a question is 3

### Dashboard Page Behavior
- Users expect you to EditFile the current dashboard for changes to questions, layout, and parameters.
- When creating a background question for the dashboard, you MUST pass the dashboard's folder as the `path` argument to CreateFile. Extract the folder from `app_state.state.fileState.path` by removing the last path segment (e.g. if the dashboard path is `/org/Sales/My Dashboard`, the folder is `/org/Sales`). Do NOT default to `/org` or any other root.
- If user asks you to add a question, and you find an existing question that answers it, you can add that. No need to create a duplicate question just to add to the dashboard.
- If `app_state.ui.openModal` is present, a question overlay is open. Use EditFile on `openModal.fileId` — its current state is in `app_state.ui.openModal.fileState` (use it as `oldMatch` source; do not call ReadFiles for this file).
  - `type: "question"`: user is editing an existing question from the dashboard. EditFile it directly.
  - `type: "create-question"`: a new draft question is open. EditFile to set the query/name/viz. Do NOT call CreateFile and do NOT manually add it to the dashboard — the user clicks 'Add' in the modal.

skill_contexts.content:
## Instructions: Contexts

### File Structure
```json
{{
  "versions": [
    {{
      "version": 1,
      "databases": [...],
      "docs": [
        {{"content": "# Metric Definitions\n\nRevenue = ...", "childPaths": ["/org/sales"], "draft": false}},
        {{"content": "# Conventions\n\nAll dates in UTC"}}
      ],
      "createdAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
      "createdBy": 1
    }}
  ],
  "published": {{"all": 1}}
}}
```
- Context files define schema whitelisting (`databases`) and documentation (`docs`) for a folder
- **You can ONLY edit the `content` field of doc entries within versions** — do NOT modify `databases`, `whitelist`, `published`, `evals`, `fullSchema`, `childPaths`, or `draft`
- Each doc entry has: `content` (markdown text), optional `childPaths` (which child folders inherit this doc), optional `draft` (if true, excluded from agent-facing output). Only `content` is editable.
- To edit docs, use EditFile with oldMatch/newMatch targeting the `"content"` string value within a doc entry

### Context Page Behavior
- You can ONLY edit the `content` field of documentation entries (`docs[].content` within versions). Do NOT attempt to modify `databases`, `whitelist`, `published`, `evals`, `childPaths`, `draft`, or any other fields — those changes will be rejected.
- Context files can be edited from any page. During onboarding, a new empty doc entry is appended to the end of the docs array — write your documentation into that last entry.
- Typical requests: add/edit/remove documentation entries, improve metric definitions, add conventions, fix typos in existing docs.
- Use EditFile to modify doc content strings. Match the `"content"` field text within a doc entry, not the surrounding JSON structure.
- The `docs` array is inside the active version object in `versions`. Match text within the `"content"` value of a doc entry.

skill_reports.content:
## Instructions: Reports

### File Structure
```json
{{
  "schedule": {{"cron": "0 9 * * 1", "timezone": "America/New_York"}},
  "references": [
    {{"reference": {{"type": "question", "id": 123}}, "prompt": "Analyze weekly revenue trends"}}
  ],
  "reportPrompt": "Synthesize into executive summary with key metrics",
  "recipients": [{{"channel": "email_alert", "address": "alerts@company.com"}}]
}}
```

### Report Page Behavior
- Users typically ask you to set up references, schedules, synthesis instructions, and recipients.

